This paper deals with path loss models for millimeter wave wireless communications in rural macrocell settings. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.IT (Information Theory), which deals with the study of communication systems and their information transmission capabilities. The paper also discusses the use of field data and simulations, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) or cs.MM (Multimedia). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of models and simulations, which could place it in the sub-categories of cs.COM (Computers and Society) or cs.MA (Multiagent Systems).
